args: Thanks for your help with those fiends,\nAnnelie.
Happy to do it, chum! ...Hmm? Hey,\nI think there's someone at the castle gate.
Excuse me! Are you Ringmaster Annelie\nand Prince {player_name}?
I'm Theo, and I'm the ringmaster of\nanother circus. ...Or I used to be, anyway.
I came to ask for your assistance.\nWould the two of you hear me out?
...What?! The Empire burned your circus\ntent to the ground?!
Yes. I fear they've started putting\nrestrictions on circuses.
The soldier told me, ＂There's no time for\nfrivolity; people's energy should be spent\nglorifying the Empire instead!＂
How dare they call what we do ＂frivolous＂!\nThey can't get away with this!
I had the same reaction at first,\nso we kept performing.
But over time, towns in fear of the Empire\nbegan to refuse us entry. The final blow\ncame when soldiers set fire to our tent.
As we were trying to work out what to do\nwith ourselves, we heard a rumor...
People said that there was a circus troupe\nhere in this very castle.
Please let us join this troupe!
None of us know any other way to live;\nperforming is all we've ever done.
We must help these poor people,\n{player_name}! Please say yes!
Of course. They're all welcome to\ncome and stay here.
*sigh* I can't believe circuses are being\nbanned now.
I didn't expect to find you out here,\nAnnelie. What's going on?
I needed some time to think.
Yes. I can't help but wonder what we\nwould do in the same situation.
And the more I think about it,\nthe more unsure I get.
Well, the purpose of a circus is to\nmake people happy, right?
So there's no way we could use it to praise\nan Empire that does nothing but spread\nmisery and sadness across the world.
But if we refuse to obey them and get\nput out of business, THAT won't make\npeople happy either.
I mean, maybe we're better off doing\nwhat the Empire wants. At least that\nway we get to keep our jobs.
I feel terrible for even having a thought\nlike that, but I just can't shake it.
I hear what you're saying, but...
Look, your dream is to make everyone\nhappy with your circus, right?
I don't see how that's possible if you\nbecome some kind of mouthpiece\nfor the Empire.
Yeah, I know that. But what am I supposed\nto do otherwise?
I mean, a flaming circus tent filled with\nangry soldiers won't exactly have folks\nrolling in the aisles.
If we submit, my performers can at least\nkeep their jobs—which is SOMETHING\npositive as opposed to nothing at all.
Er, we don't fight now.\nNot really, anyway.
Sure, Fritz and I hold our own in battle,\nbut I can't say the same about most\nof the other troupe members.
Weapons aren't the only way to fight.
Your troupe can fight the Empire\nin its own way.
What's the greatest weapon\nyour people have?
Uh... Wow. I have literally never\nconsidered that before right now.
I don't think we even HAVE a weapon.
All we do is make people happy no\nmatter how bad things ge...
Wait. That's totally your point, isn't it?
How could I have forgotten that?\nI say it all the time, after all...
The show must go on!\nTHAT'S our weapon!
If the Empire is going to bring sadness\ninto the world, we'll just follow behind\n'em and make everyone happy again!
If people try to ban what we're doing,\nwe'll USE that power to win them over!
That's right! The circus is quite strong\nin its own way.
Think about how far you're willing to go—\nfiguratively AND literally—in order to\nmake sure every single person is happy.
You have the power to cheer people in\nthe depths of their despair.
And above all, you have the drive to make\nsure the show goes on no matter what.
So long as you keep fighting,\nthe Empire will never defeat you.
Of course, from a practical perspective,\nwe'll always be around to help protect\nyour shows and people.
No stupid Empire will get away with\ncalling OUR circus ＂frivolous!＂
We're going to fight them,\nand we're going to win!
